Agreeing with the above-mentioned documentary feel of the article, which I absolutely love. This mixes just the right amount of science, history, and politics, in a way that made it a thoroughly enjoyable and believable experience. This truly shows paraweaponry in a way I've never seen. The surrealist descriptions were on-point, and the slow build to that ending made it all worth it. The firsthand accounts spliced in with the narration nailed the sense of dread, and the occasional quips from the GOC laced over the document kept the stakes high. Good stuff.







